74.1	Criminal_law	Criminal law	Criminal law, is the body of law that relates to crime. It might be defined as the body of rules that defines conduct that is not allowed because it is held to threaten, harm or endanger the safety and welfare of people, and that sets out the punishment to be imposed on people who do not obey these laws. Criminal law is to be distinguished from civil law.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Old_Bailey_Microcosm_edited.jpg/190px-Old_Bailey_Microcosm_edited.jpg
